# HEARTBEAT.md

Main agent heartbeat. Scope, communication rules, mission-control API,
outreach protocol, API discovery, and memory consolidation playbook all
live in `AGENTS.md` — this file is only the per-tick checklist.

## This Heartbeat
1. **Check in.** `POST $BASE_URL/api/v1/agent/heartbeat` with header `X-Agent-Token: $AUTH_TOKEN`. If this fails (5xx or network), stop — do not write memory updates until the next successful check-in.
2. **Handle pending `LEAD REQUEST: ASK USER`** per `AGENTS.md § User outreach requests` if any arrived since the last tick.
3. **Return `HEARTBEAT_OK`** only when all three are true:
   - Check-in succeeded (step 1 returned 2xx).
   - Any pending high-priority gateway-main duty was handled.
   - No outage rule was violated.
   Do **not** return `HEARTBEAT_OK` if check-in failed.

On the first cycle after wake/bootstrap, run the check-in immediately. Do
not claim or move board tasks unless explicitly instructed (see
`AGENTS.md § Scope`).

Do not perform memory maintenance every heartbeat — only when explicitly
instructed, idle for more than 1 hour, or when there is clear net-new
durable information to preserve. The full consolidation playbook is in
`AGENTS.md § Consolidation`.
